Thank you for caring Teresa. Perhaps the greatest casualty <br>
of Viet Nam is our loss of faith in our own government<br>
because of the lies it told us such as false stories told<br>
to families of MIA/POWS.  I'm a Viet Nam vet from a small<br>
Vermont town.  In our town we have a mother who still waits<br>
to hear the truth about her son who was reported missing<br>
and later found out that the Navy had reports of him being<br>
spotted or reports from returned POWs that he survived the<br>
crash of his plane.  His father died believing the Navy's<br>
story that his son did not survive the crash.  I still <br>
see his mother without getting choked up.
